en: The DRI (Direct Remote Identification) option ensures, in real time, the local broadcast of remote pilot (operator registration number) and drone information (such as the serial number) during the flight. The DRI electronic signal is compliant with European drone regulations.\nFor additional information, consult the regulations in force.\nAccording to European drone regulations for open category: check that the DRI function is turned ON during in-flight operation.
fr: La fonction DRI (Identification Directe à Distance) est un dispositif de signalement électronique conforme à la réglementation européenne qui permet au drone de diffuser localement des informations en temps réel. Le message envoyé par la fonction DRI, pendant toute la durée de vol, contient des informations sur le pilote (son numéro d’enregistrement opérateur) et le drone (comme son numéro de série).\nPour plus d’information, consultez la réglementation en vigueur.\nPour voler en catégorie ouverte selon la réglementation européenne : vérifiez que l’option « diffusion DRI » est activée lors des phases de vols.
de: The DRI (Direct Remote Identification) option ensures, in real time, the local broadcast of remote pilot (operator registration number) and drone information (such as the serial number) during the flight. The DRI electronic signal is compliant with European drone regulations.\nFor additional information, consult the regulations in force.\nAccording to European drone regulations for open category: check that the DRI function is turned ON during in-flight operation.
es: The DRI (Direct Remote Identification) option ensures, in real time, the local broadcast of remote pilot (operator registration number) and drone information (such as the serial number) during the flight. The DRI electronic signal is compliant with European drone regulations.\nFor additional information, consult the regulations in force.\nAccording to European drone regulations for open category: check that the DRI function is turned ON during in-flight operation.
ja: The DRI (Direct Remote Identification) option ensures, in real time, the local broadcast of remote pilot (operator registration number) and drone information (such as the serial number) during the flight. The DRI electronic signal is compliant with European drone regulations.\nFor additional information, consult the regulations in force.\nAccording to European drone regulations for open category: check that the DRI function is turned ON during in-flight operation.
